# üñß Networking Commands Cheat Sheet

In DevOps, networking commands are essential for troubleshooting, monitoring, and securing systems. Below is a list of commonly used networking commands along with their descriptions and examples.

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ **ping** - Check Connectivity
Used to check whether a remote system is reachable.
ping google.com

2Ô∏è‚É£ traceroute / tracert - Trace Packet Routes
Shows the path a packet takes to reach a destination.

Linux/macOS:
traceroute google.com

Windows:
tracert google.com

3Ô∏è‚É£ netstat - View Network Statistics
Displays active network connections and listening ports.
netstat -tulnp
-t TCP connections
-u UDP connections
-l Listening ports
-n Show numerical addresses
-p Show process using the connection


4Ô∏è‚É£ curl - Make HTTP Requests
Used for interacting with web services.

curl -I https://www.example.com
-I Fetch headers only
-X Specify HTTP method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

Example:
curl -X GET https://api.example.com/data

5Ô∏è‚É£ dig / nslookup - DNS Lookup
Retrieve DNS records for a domain.

Linux/macOS: dig google.com
Windows: nslookup google.com
Used to troubleshoot domain name resolution.


